<TITLE> DESA engineer charged with taking bribe </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Sunday framed charges against a Dhaka Electric Supply Authority engineer for allegedly taking bribes. Judge Amar Kumar Roy of the Special Judges' Court-2 framed charges against DESA sub-assistant engineer (sales and distribution) Sheikh Quamruzzaman. The court scheduled the deposition for Nov 15. Twenty-three state's witnesses are expected give depositions. Quamruzzaman's house caretaker Golam Mostafa filed the bribery case with Paltan Police Station on April 18. According to case details, the accused demanded Tk 35,000 to connect a severed electricity meter at a Shantinagar house. On April 15, Quamruzzaman connected the line in exchange for Tk 15,000. He was caught by RAB-3 on April 17 while attempting to obtain the remaining Tk 20,000. Anticorruption Commission assistant director Aminul Islam pressed the chargesheet against Quamruzzaman after an investigation. bdnew
